SIMPLE: soever
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soever
<hw>So*ev"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A word compounded of <xex>so</xex>
and <xex>ever</xex>, used in composition with <xex>who</xex>,
<xex>what</xex>, <xex>where</xex>, <xex>when</xex>, <xex>how</xex>,
etc., and indicating any out of all possible or supposable persons,
things, places, times, ways, etc. It is sometimes used separate from the
pronoun or adverb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For unto whom<qex>soever</qex> much is given, of him shall be much
required.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xii. 48.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What great thing <qex>soever</qex> a man proposed to do in his
life, he should think of achieving it by fifty.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sofa</ent>⟦br⟧
